Description:
Ballistics of 115x728R 3UBM5 round, with the 3BM6 steel core APFSDS-T shot, fired from the U-5TS tank gun (GRAU index 2A20), chiefly employed on the T-62 tank. Introduction date is some point from 1964 to 1966, with the round revised in 1966-1968 to eliminate the armor-piercing cap. Modelling based on the following information (АРТИЛЛЕРИЙСКИЕ МЕТАТЕЛЬНЫЕ ЗАРЯДЫ):

Barrel Length:      5840 mm
Cartridge Length:    723 mm
Projectile Mass:    5.34 kg
Projectile Travel:  5117 mm
Peak Pressure:      3650 kgf/cm² breech, copper crusher gauge (1.12 x 0.09805), converts to 400 MPa.
Muzzle Velocity:    1615 m/s
Chambrage:          1.37 from 枪炮内弹道学 (2014).
Propellant:          8.1 kg, 4.9 kg 12/7 + 3.2 kg 18/1
